	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9740257929540><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Maxed out skills</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Nov 12th 5:43 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, a number of times on this discussion board I have seen reference to maxing out skills.&nbsp;&nbsp;This brings up a couple of questions (and yes.  I'm new to this.  Only been playing about 2 months.)<br><br>1) How do you know when you've maxed out a skill for your current level?<br><br>2) How DO you max out a skill?  My monk is now level 7.  He has YET to get a skill to the point that it won't go up, again.  I thought maybe if I fought green mobs I could get H2H to max out without going up a level.  Well, that didn't work.  It never went up.  Can someone clarify?<br><br>And a completely different question that is WAY off this subject.<br><br>My Mend is at Below Average and almost never works.  90% of the time if it does something other than fail, it causes me damage.  I see people with the Mend ability at awful, and it works on a regular basis for them.  Why is this?  What is wrong?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
